A vintage 1960s-style illustration depicting a designer's workshop where a craftsperson carefully sculpts a glowing, translucent human silhouette seated at a desk, surrounded by floating color swatches, wireframe sketches pinned to cork boards, and scattered sticky notes in warm yellows and oranges. The scene has a warm amber palette with soft cream backgrounds, subtle paper textures, and retro halftone dot patterns. In the foreground, an array of drafting tools—compasses, rulers, colored pencils—fan out artistically. The human figure at the center emanates a soft golden aura, symbolizing the user being placed at the heart of the design process. Mid-century modern furniture elements and an old wooden drafting table complete the nostalgic atmosphere of thoughtful, human-centered craftsmanship.
